@node Database Schema
@chapter Database Schema

This chapter describes the database schema used by Xeetapus.  The
database is implemented using SQLite, a lightweight, serverless database
engine.  All application data is stored in a single file.

@menu
* Introduction::                 Overview of the database.
* Users Table::                  User accounts and profiles.
* Posts Table::                  User posts (xeets).
* Social Tables::                Likes, follows, comments, and reposts.
* Notifications Table::          User notifications.
* Communities Table::            Topic-based groups.
* Messages Table::               Direct messaging.
* Polls Table::                  Poll system.
* Blocking and Muting::          User restrictions.
* Drafts Table::                  Saved drafts.
* LLM Configuration::             AI provider settings.
* Indexes::                      Database indexes for performance.
* Migrations::                   Schema versioning.
* Backup and Restore::            Data protection.
@end menu

@node Introduction
@section Introduction

The Xeetapus database is stored as a single SQLite file.  By default,
this file is named @file{xeetapus.db} and is located in the backend
directory.  The location may be changed using the
@env{XEETAPUS_DB_PATH} environment variable.

SQLite was chosen for its simplicity.  There is no database server to
install or configure; the database is simply a file on disk.  This
makes backups straightforward: simply copy the file to another location.

The database schema is versioned through a migration system.  Migrations
are applied automatically when the server starts.  New schema changes are
recorded as migrations in the source code.

@node Users Table
@section Users Table

The @code{users} table stores user account information.

@float Table, tab:users
@caption{users}
@multitable @columnfractions 0.2 0.15 0.25 0.4
@headitem Column @tab Type @tab Constraints @tab Description
@item id @tab INTEGER @tab PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT @tab Unique user ID
@item username @tab TEXT @tab UNIQUE, NOT NULL @tab Username (3-20 chars)
@item email @tab TEXT @tab UNIQUE, NOT NULL @tab Email address
@item password_hash @tab TEXT @tab NOT NULL @tab PBKDF2 hash of password
@item display_name @tab TEXT @tab @tab Public display name
@item bio @tab TEXT @tab @tab User biography
@item avatar_url @tab TEXT @tab @tab URL to avatar image
@item created_at @tab DATETIME @tab DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP @tab Account creation time
@item updated_at @tab DATETIME @tab DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP @tab Last modification time
@end multitable
@end float

Indexes are created on the @code{username} and @code{email} columns to
ensure fast lookups during authentication and profile retrieval.

@example
INSERT INTO users (username, email, password_hash)
VALUES ('johndoe', 'john@@example.com', '$pbkdf2-sha256$...');
@end example

@node Posts Table
@section Posts Table

The @code{posts} table stores user-generated content.

@float Table, tab:posts
@caption{posts}
@multitable @columnfractions 0.2 0.15 0.25 0.4
@headitem Column @tab Type @tab Constraints @tab Description
@item id @tab INTEGER @tab PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT @tab Unique post ID
@item user_id @tab INTEGER @tab NOT NULL, FK(users.id) @tab Author's user ID
@item content @tab TEXT @tab NOT NULL @tab Post content (max 280 chars)
@item media_urls @tab TEXT @tab @tab JSON array of media URLs
@item reply_to_id @tab INTEGER @tab FK(posts.id) @tab Parent post (for replies)
@item poll_id @tab INTEGER @tab FK(polls.id) @tab Attached poll (optional)
@item created_at @tab DATETIME @tab DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP @tab Creation time
@end multitable
@end float

Posts support several features:

@itemize @bullet
@item
Regular posts containing text content.

@item
Replies to other posts (indicated by @code{reply_to_id}).

@item
Posts with attached media (stored as a JSON array in @code{media_urls}).

@item
Posts with attached polls (indicated by @code{poll_id}).
@end itemize

Indexes are created on @code{user_id} for user lookups, @code{created_at}
for timeline queries, and @code{reply_to_id} for loading replies.

@node Social Tables
@section Social Tables

Several tables track social relationships and interactions.

@float Table, tab:likes
@caption{likes}
@multitable @columnfractions 0.2 0.15 0.25 0.4
@headitem Column @tab Type @tab Constraints @tab Description
@item id @tab INTEGER @tab PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT @tab Unique like ID
