@node Notifications Table
@section Notifications Table

The @code{notifications} table tracks events that users should be
informed about.

@float Table, tab:notifications
@caption{notifications}
@multitable @columnfractions 0.2 0.15 0.25 0.4
@headitem Column @tab Type @tab Constraints @tab Description
@item id @tab INTEGER @tab PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT @tab Unique notification ID
@item user_id @tab INTEGER @tab NOT NULL, FK(users.id) @tab Recipient user
@item actor_id @tab INTEGER @tab NOT NULL, FK(users.id) @tab User who triggered event
@item type @tab TEXT @tab NOT NULL @tab Event type
@item post_id @tab INTEGER @tab FK(posts.id) @tab Related post (if applicable)
@item read @tab INTEGER @tab DEFAULT 0 @tab Read status (0 = unread, 1 = read)
@item created_at @tab DATETIME @tab DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP @tab Creation time
@end multitable
@end float

The @code{type} column indicates the nature of the notification:

@table @asis
@item like
Another user liked one of your posts.

@item follow
Another user followed you.

@item mention
Another user mentioned you in a post.

@item comment
Another user commented on your post.

@item repost
Another user reposted your post.
@end table

@node Communities Table
@section Communities Table

The @code{communities} table stores topic-based groups.

@float Table, tab:communities
@caption{communities}
@multitable @columnfractions 0.2 0.15 0.25 0.4
@headitem Column @tab Type @tab Constraints @tab Description
@item id @tab INTEGER @tab PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT @tab Unique community ID
@item name @tab TEXT @tab UNIQUE, NOT NULL @tab Community name
@item description @tab TEXT @tab @tab Community description
@item created_by @tab INTEGER @tab NOT NULL, FK(users.id) @tab Creator user ID
@item created_at @tab DATETIME @tab DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP @tab Creation time
@end multitable
@end float

Community memberships are tracked in a separate @code{community_members}
table (not shown).  Posts can optionally belong to a community via the
@code{community_id} column in the @code{posts} table.

@node Messages Table
@section Messages Table

The @code{messages} table stores direct messages between users.

@float Table, tab:messages
@caption{messages}
@multitable @columnfractions 0.2 0.15 0.25 0.4
@headitem Column @tab Type @tab Constraints @tab Description
@item id @tab INTEGER @tab PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT @tab Unique message ID
@item conversation_id @tab INTEGER @tab NOT NULL, FK(conversations.id) @tab Conversation
@item sender_id @tab INTEGER @tab NOT NULL, FK(users.id) @tab Sender user ID
@item content @tab TEXT @tab NOT NULL @tab Message content
@item media_urls @tab TEXT @tab @tab JSON array of media URLs
@item read @tab INTEGER @tab DEFAULT 0 @tab Read status (0 = unread, 1 = read)
@item created_at @tab DATETIME @tab DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP @tab Send time
@end multitable
@end float

Conversations are stored in a separate @code{conversations} table that
tracks the participants.  This design allows efficient listing of
conversations without scanning all messages.

