@node Blocking and Muting
@section Blocking and Muting

The @code{blocks} and @code{mutes} tables track user restrictions.

@float Table, tab:blocks
@caption{blocks}
@multitable @columnfractions 0.2 0.15 0.25 0.4
@headitem Column @tab Type @tab Constraints @tab Description
@item id @tab INTEGER @tab PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT @tab Unique block ID
@item blocker_id @tab INTEGER @tab NOT NULL, FK(users.id) @tab User who blocked
@item blocked_id @tab INTEGER @tab NOT NULL, FK(users.id) @tab Blocked user
@item created_at @tab DATETIME @tab DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP @tab Block time
@end multitable
@end float

@float Table, tab:mutes
@caption{mutes}
@multitable @columnfractions 0.2 0.15 0.25 0.4
@headitem Column @tab Type @tab Constraints @tab Description
@item id @tab INTEGER @tab PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT @tab Unique mute ID
@item muter_id @tab INTEGER @tab NOT NULL, FK(users.id) @tab User who muted
@item muted_id @tab INTEGER @tab NOT NULL, FK(users.id) @tab Muted user
@item created_at @tab DATETIME @tab DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP @tab Mute time
@end multitable
@end float

Both tables have unique constraints preventing duplicate relationships.

Blocking is more restrictive than muting: blocked users cannot see your
content or interact with you.  Muted users are simply hidden from your
timeline without their knowledge.

